description:
This is a blended image consisting of data I took of M45 from my Bortle 8/9 skies awhile back, and images I took on 4/4 of Venus mingling with the Seven Sisters. I used a homemade mask to stop down the ED80 to make Venus look better than a blown out misshapen blob, it gave me nice diffraction spikes too!

M45 Details:
Captured 01/01/2020, 231x60s, 3.9 hours
Scope: William Optics GT81 with FLAT6AIII .8x Flattener/Reducer
Camera: ZWO ASI294MC Pro
Mount: Rainbow Astro RST135
Filter: Optolong L-eNhance LP filter

Venus/M45 Details:
Captured 04/04/2020, 20x10s
Scope: Skywatcher Esprit 80ED Pro with Starizona APEX-S .65x reducer
Camera: ZWO ASI533MC Pro
Mount: Rainbow Astro RST135
Filter: Optolong L-Pro 

Pre and post processing in Pixinsight. Separate images aligned with StarAlignment. GAME script was awesome in making the required masks. Blended the long exposure image of M45 with the Venus/M45 image stack using Pixelmath.
title: The Goddess of Beauty and Love hangs with The Seven Sisters
